Q. When did you take a risk, make a mistake, or fail? How did you respond, and how did you grow from that experience?
Ans-   S :  We were doing a project in sap, where we have to work on tablescript and tabscrpit which is an inbuilt functionality, but we are making 
            are making a customised screen as given in SRS document
       T:   It was like a view having a various functionality to place an order, to make quotation, etc and whenever a user fill the 
            table it make a contact with database to know the availablity, its price , specifications and all. as general if you 
            make this in other techmology its not a big deal but when you make it in a sap,a lot of internal modules get 
            triggered So this was the situation after filling up the details about any product and press Enter, it go and 
            performs a four modules, and they were handling the integrated core sap functions, and we were still struggling 
            to do that task, and that when we commit a mistake. 
           
           
           


